-- Russian Stocks Jump to Six-Month High on China’s Europe Pledge
-- B y   D e n i s   M a t e r n o v s k y
-- 2012-02-15T15:23:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-15/russian-stocks-jump-to-six-month-high-on-china-s-europe-pledge.html
Russian stocks rose for a third day,
driving the benchmark gauge to the highest level in more than
six months, as  China  resolved to help more with European bailout
efforts, lifting equities globally.  The 30-stock Micex jumped 1.1 percent to 1,579.38 by the
6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, its highest since Aug. 5. Russian
depositary receipts of  United Co. Rusal (RUALR) , the world’s biggest
aluminum producer, added 2.8 percent. Oil producer OAO
Surgutneftegas gained 2 percent. The dollar-denominated  RTS
Index (RTSI$)  rose 1.1 percent to 1,661.36, its highest level since
Sept. 8.  Emerging-market stocks climbed and oil,  Russia ’s main
export revenue earner, rose as much as 1 percent to $101.76 a
barrel in  New York , advancing from a two-day low. China pledged
to help resolve  Europe ’s debt crisis through the European
Financial Stability Facility and European Stability Mechanism.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN) , the country’s biggest oil company, rose 1.7
percent to 218.94 rubles, while  OAO Lukoil (LKOH) , Russia’s second-
largest oil producer, advanced 0.8 percent to 1,879 rubles.  The  Micex (INDEXCF)  is up 13 percent this year and trades at 6.1
times analysts’ earnings estimates for member companies.
 Brazil ’s Bovespa index is valued at 10.5 times estimated
earnings, the Shanghai Composite Index trades at 9.7 times, and
the BSE India Sensitive Index has a ratio of 16.2.  OAO Sberbank (SBER) , Russia’s biggest lender, rose 0.7 percent to
97.06 rubles, its highest closing level since Aug. 4. Shares of
VTB Group, Russia’s second-biggest lender, added 1.3 percent to
7.18 kopeks, a weekly high.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Denis Maternovsky in Moscow at 
